      <p>Most common type. Every pallet is accessible. Low cost per position. Good for variety.</p>

      <h3>Drive-In Racking</h3>
      <p>Forklift drives into racks. High density. Fewer aisles needed. Good for same items.</p>

      <h3>Push Back Racking</h3>
      <p>Pallets push back on rails. 2-5 pallets deep. Good density with some selectivity.</p>

      <h3>Cantilever Racking</h3>
      <p>For long items. Pipes, lumber, sheets. No front posts. Good for odd-shaped items.</p>

